<subSubSection id="87B46525FFF8FFE2FF6956A1FDE72ED0" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF8FFE2FF6956A1FECE2E3C" blockId="7.[189,310,1261,1287]" box="[189,310,1261,1287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">
<heading id="945981C2FFF8FFE2FF6956A1FECE2E3C" bold="true" box="[189,310,1261,1287]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF8FFE2FF6956A1FECE2E3C" bold="true" box="[189,310,1261,1287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF8FFE2FF695751FDE72ED0" blockId="7.[188,1400,1308,1515]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF8FFE2FE935751FE2E2E0C" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[327,470,1309,1335]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aceitillar" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF8FFE2FE935751FE2E2E0C" box="[327,470,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">N. aceitillar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF8FFE2FE095751FDC02E0C" box="[477,568,1309,1335]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF8FFE2FCC35751FC962E0C" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[791,878,1309,1335]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF8FFE2FCC35751FC962E0C" box="[791,878,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">N. bani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF8FFE2FCA15751FC282E0C" box="[885,976,1309,1335]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF8FFE2FC345751FBD22E0C" box="[992,1066,1309,1335]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[186,229,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[224,1357,780,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-109@11.[189,1399,752,1870]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Neostasina bani sp. nov., A−C: holotype, ♂ (MNHNPEJM), D−E: paratype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view.C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607918/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">Figs 4</figureCitation>
D−E, 5E−G) by the epigyne with MS heart-shaped, with anterior median indentation and by the SP packed within a sclerotized structure with internal ducts with more than one twist. They are distinguished from those of the latter species by the indentation extending posteriorly, surpassing half MS length (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF8FFE2FBE657C5FB772E98" box="[1074,1167,1417,1443]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,233,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[225,1377,510,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-61@8.[210,1377,500,1882]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 1. Neostasina aceitillar sp. nov., A−B: paratype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM), C−D: holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607910/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF8FFE2FB4F57C5FB392E98" box="[1179,1217,1417,1443]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[188,232,907,933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1329,308,796]" captionTargetId="figure-249@9.[189,1399,286,829]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 2. Neostasina aceitillar sp. nov., A−B: holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: am = anterior margin; ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607912" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607912/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">2A</figureCitation>
) (not extending posteriorly in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF8FFE2FEB557E2FE4F2EFC" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[353,439,1453,1479]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF8FFE2FEB557E2FE4F2EFC" box="[353,439,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">N. bani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF8FFE2FE6A57E1FDE22EFC" box="[446,538,1453,1479]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) and by the SP bearing only two twists (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF8FFE2FC2657E1FBAA2EFC" box="[1010,1106,1453,1479]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[191,233,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[225,1377,510,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-61@8.[210,1377,500,1882]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 1. Neostasina aceitillar sp. nov., A−B: paratype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM), C−D: holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607910/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">Figs 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF8FFE2FB8B57E1FB952EFC" box="[1119,1133,1453,1479]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[188,232,907,933]" captionTargetBox="[219,1329,308,796]" captionTargetId="figure-249@9.[189,1399,286,829]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 2. Neostasina aceitillar sp. nov., A−B: holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: am = anterior margin; ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607912" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607912/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">2</figureCitation>
B−C) (three in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF8FFE2FAF457E2FA8E2EFC" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[1312,1398,1453,1479]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF8FFE2FAF457E2FA8E2EFC" box="[1312,1398,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="173">N. bani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF8FFE2FF69579DFEE42ED0" box="[189,284,1489,1515]" pageId="7" pageNumber="173" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
